<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Miracle 88, Starzz 80  </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
   SALT LAKE CITY (AP) -- Shannon Johnson scored 19 points and had
12 assists to lead the Orlando Miracle to an 88-80 victory over the
Utah Starzz on Tuesday night.
</P>
<P>
   Johnson hit a 3-pointer to tie it at 70 with 5:07 left, then
came up with a steal, a driving layup and a free throw to give the
Miracle (5-3) a 73-70 lead with 4:31 remaining.
</P>
<P>
   Orlando, which outscored the Starzz (3-5) 30-13 in the final
9:22, never trailed again.
</P>
<P>
   Nykesha Sales scored 18 points Taj McWilliams added 17, Cintia
dos Santos 14 and Adrienne Johnson 10 for the Miracle.
</P>
<P>
   The Starzz, who led 47-42 at halftime, were led by Natalie
Williams with 19 points and 14 rebounds. Adrienne Goodson added 17
points and Margo Dydek 13 points, eight rebounds and seven blocks.
</P>
<P>
   Utah outrebounded Orlando 36-23 but had 19 turnovers, which the
Miracle converted into 25 points.
</P>
</TEXT>
