<SUBHEAD>
House GOP Seeks $16M for Campaign
</SUBHEAD>
<P>
   WASHINGTON (AP)-- House Republican leaders will demand GOP lawmakers raise
$16 million for use in key contested races this fall, officials said Tuesday
night. They intend to hold the rank and file accountable through control of
chairmanships and committee assignments in 2001. Any Republican who declines to
assume responsibility for his allotted fund-raising quota will be asked to
''call the speaker (House Speaker Dennis Hastert, R-Ill.), set up a personal
meeting to tell him why,'' according to material prepared for a session of GOP
members on Wednesday morning.
</P>
<SUBHEAD>
Suharto Family Negotiating With Govt.
</SUBHEAD>
<P>
   NEW YORK (AP) -- Indonesia's president said Tuesday that family members of
former autocratic President Suharto are negotiating with the government to
return any alleged ill-gotten gains from the years of Suharto's rule. The family
''would like to give back the fortune ... to the state,'' President Abdurrahman
Wahid said during a speech to the American Indonesian Chamber of Commerce in New
York. He said negotiations are under way. Suharto's family and lawyers could not
immediately be reached for comment.
