<HEADLINE> Storm 69, Sparks 59, OT  </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
   SEATTLE (AP) -- Edna Campbell tied her career high with 22
points, including seven in overtime, as the expansion Seattle Storm
beat the Los Angeles Sparks 69-59 Tuesday night for their first
home victory.
</P>
<P>
   Simone Edwards and Quacy Barnes scored 10 points each for the
Storm, who relinquished a seven-point lead in the last three
minutes of regulation, but dominated the overtime.
</P>
<P>
   Campbell hit a 3-pointer on the Storm's first possession, and
Seattle outscored Los Angeles 14-4 in overtime.
</P>
<P>
   Ukari Figgs made two free throws with 8.9 seconds left in
regulation to tie it at 55. Michelle Edwards, acquired in a trade
with Cleveland on Sunday, had a chance to win the game but missed a
17-footer as time expired.
</P>
<P>
   Campbell's three free throws gave Seattle a 52-45 lead, but the
Sparks outscored the Storm 10-3 the last three minutes.
</P>
<P>
   Lisa Leslie, the Sparks' leading scorer and rebounder, fouled
out with 3:14 left and finished with eight points on 3-for-12
shooting and had five rebounds.
</P>
<P>
   Edwards added 10 points and four assists for Seattle.
</P>
</TEXT>
