<HEADLINE> Reds' Aaron Boone Struck by Pitch  </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
   SAN FRANCISCO (AP) -- Cincinnati's Aaron Boone was struck in the
face Tuesday night by a pitch while batting in the seventh inning
and was taken to the hospital.
</P>
<P>
   Boone fell to the ground in pain after being hit by the pitch
from San Francisco's Russ Ortiz as teammates and trainers rushed to
tend to him. He appeared to be bleeding from the nose.
</P>
<P>
   Players from both sides and the crowd at Pacific Bell Park
watched in hushed silence as he lay face down on the ground. After
several minutes, he was helped to his feet and the crowd gave him a
warm round of applause.
</P>
<P>
   Boone then walked off the field with help from trainers, a towel
wrapped around his face.
</P>
<P>
   The Reds third baseman was taken to St. Francis Hospital for
precautionary tests and X-rays.
</P>
<P>
   Ortiz was lifted in favor of Felix Rodriguez, and Juan Castro
went in as a pinch-runner for Boone.
</P>
