<HEADLINE> 8 Hurt When Propane Tank Explodes  </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
   CASTRO VALLEY, Calif. (AP) -- A propane explosion and fire in a
cooking tent at a religious gathering injured eight people,
including six who were hospitalized in critical condition with
severe burns.
</P>
<P>
   The eight victims had been cooking for followers of Mata
Amritanandamayi, a religious leader visiting from India. About 200
to 300 people were scattered around the area Tuesday afternoon.
</P>
<P>
   The six in the hospital have second- and third-degree burns over
20 percent to 30 percent of their bodies, and were listed in
critical condition. The two others suffered minor injuries, said
Capt. Dave Wheeler of the Alameda County Fire Department.
</P>
<P>
   Fire investigators were trying to determine what triggered the
explosion. The fire burned two acres of grassland and was
extinguished in under an hour.
</P>
<P>
   Investigators were also checking to see if the group had the
appropriate permits to set up in the rural area.
</P>
