<HEADLINE> Democratic Co-Chairs Appointed  </HEADLINE>
By WILL LESTER
<TEXT>
<P>
   WASHINGTON (AP) -- Sen. Richard Durbin of Illinois and
Minneapolis Mayor Sharon Sayles Belton have been named as co-chairs
of the Democratic Party's Platform Committee.
</P>
<P>
   North Carolina Gov. James Hunt and Maryland Lt. Gov. Kathleen
Kennedy Townsend will be in charge of the panel responsible for
drafting the document, party officials said Tuesday.
</P>
<P>
   Democratic officials want the platform to emphasize ''progress
and prosperity'' -- the theme of a three-week tour launched Tuesday
by presidential contender Al Gore -- fiscal discipline, education,
health care and safer communities. They expect few battles drafting
the document and have sought public input via the Internet.
</P>
<P>
   The platform, which spells out the party's goals and principles,
will be ratified during the Democratic National Convention, Aug.
14-17 in Los Angeles.
</P>
<P>
   The committee leadership represents geographic, gender and
ethnic diversity, an important theme at every Democratic National
Convention.
</P>
<P>
   Durbin, who hails from a key battleground state, has been
mentioned as a possible running mate for Gore and is viewed as
strong on child health issues. Belton has long been involved in
women's issues and co-founded a shelter for battered women. Hunt is
a Southern moderate in his fourth term and a possible vice
presidential pick. Townsend is a daughter of the late Robert F.
Kennedy.
</P>
<P>
   Committee vice chairs are Florida Attorney General Bob
Butterworth; Sen. Patty Murray of Washington state; Sen. Jack Reed
of Rhode Island; Gov. Pedro Rosello of Puerto Rico; and Del.
Eleanor Holmes Norton of Washington, D.C.
</P>
<P>
   Members include Sen. Charles Schumer of New York; Vermont Gov.
Howard Dean; Rep. Karen Thurman of Florida; Rep. Eddie Bernice
Johnson of Texas; and former Housing Secretary Henry Cisneros.
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
<TRAILER> AP-NY-06-14-00 0209 </TRAILER>
