<DOCNO> APW20000614.0056 </DOCNO>
<DOCTYPE> NEWS STORY </DOCTYPE>
<DATE_TIME> 2000-06-14 02:43 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Raptors Fire Carter As Coach  </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
   TORONTO (AP) -- It wasn't wins and losses that got Butch Carter
fired. It was just time for him to go.
</P>
<P>
   ''I did not want out of Toronto, all right? I wanted out of a
bad situation,'' Carter said Tuesday after his dismissal as Raptors
coach. ''I think I've given this city and Raptor fans a lot to be
proud of.
</P>
<P>
   ''It's one of the best cities I've ever lived in in my life, but
I didn't want to be part of a bad situation that had been
created.''
</P>
<P>
   General manager Glen Grunwald praised Carter for his work in
turning around the team, but said the coach was paying the price
for the cloud of controversy that swirled around the team in recent
months.
</P>
<P>
   ''In my perception of the things that have gone on, it would
have been best for everybody involved that something changed,''
Carter said. ''What it boiled down to is that they were willing to
stand behind me, but that would not have been in the best interest
of everything we've accumulated here.''
</P>
<P>
   There was no immediate word on Carter's successor.
</P>
<P>
   Carter made comments and actions that led to criticism from the
team's veterans and perhaps will cost the club a chance to re-sign
young forward Tracy McGrady.
</P>
<P>
   Grunwald put an end to the distraction that Carter had become,
saying there was no other alternative.
</P>
<P>
   ''We have a great team, we have some great guys in our locker
room,'' he said. ''We have great ownership. We play in a great
arena before some magnificent fans. Our future is very bright.
</P>
<P>
   ''But I think we've lost track of that story a little bit in
some of these off-the-court things and I think we need to refocus
upon that and keep improving.''
</P>
<P>
   Carter, who seemed relieved at his afternoon news conference,
led the Raptors to their first postseason berth. He was rewarded in
December with a contract extension through the 2002-03 season.
</P>
<P>
   Team president Richard Peddie declined to discuss details of the
settlement.
</P>
<P>
   Carter, who called his coaching style ''workaholic,'' was
obviously not happy at the way some team beefs were aired outside
the locker room and in the media. But he made plenty of news
himself.
</P>
<P>
   In a book written with his brother Cris, the star receiver of
the Minnesota Vikings, he attacked Indiana coach Bob Knight for his
behavior while Butch Carter played there. He sued former Raptors
and current New York Knicks center Marcus Camby, who calling him a
liar. Carter dropped the lawsuit after his legal challenge received
widespread criticism.
</P>
<P>
   The coach made headlines again after a report he asked for
Grunwald's title in his annual job review before Grunwald and
Peddie. Carter said he did not want Grunwald's power, only his
title for added influence in dealings with free agents.
</P>
<P>
   Carter also came under fire from veterans Antonio Davis and
Charles Oakley when he said there was a lack of leadership in the
locker room.
</P>
<P>
   Perhaps the last straw came last week when McGrady, on the verge
of free agency, cited the veterans' dissatisfaction with Carter and
ensuing turmoil as reasons why he wouldn't be back in Toronto.
</P>
<P>
   ''It is clear that this change, while disappointing to me on a
personal and professional level, is necessary if we are to continue
to build towards an NBA championship,'' Grunwald said.
</P>
<P>
   On the issue of McGrady's future, Carter said: ''The kid is
smart enough to make his own decision.''
</P>
<P>
   ''Signing Tracy McGrady was no slam dunk regardless,'' he added.
</P>
<P>
   Under Carter, the Raptors finished third in the Central Division
with a 45-37 record. The team was eliminated in a first-round
playoff sweep by the Knicks.
</P>
<P>
   Carter noted the club played ''without a center and ... point
guard.''
</P>
<P>
   Carter was also seen as instrumental in grooming McGrady and
Vince Carter, the two young stars of the team.
</P>
<P>
   ''A young coach took a bunch of guys who were unhappy ... and we
made it work here,'' Butch Carter said.
</P>
<P>
   Carter was appointed head coach on June 12, 1998, after being
hired as interim coach on Feb. 13, following Darrell Walker's
resignation. He joined the team as an assistant coach before the
team's third season.
</P>
<P>
   Carter's regular-season record with the Raptors was 73-92.
</P>
<P>
   He followed Brendan Malone and Walker as head coaches with the
Raptors, who joined the league in 1995-96. Before joining the
Raptors, he was an assistant coach with the Milwaukee Bucks from
1991-96.
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
