<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Celebrity Spotlight &AMP; Birthdays  </HEADLINE>
By The Associated Press	   
<TEXT>
<P>
   In the birthday spotlight:
</P>
<P>
   Former Beatle Paul McCartney has donated $1 million to the
Arizona Cancer Center to establish a breast cancer research
endowment named in honor of his late wife. McCartney has also given
$1 million to the Memorial Sloan-Kettering Cancer Center in New
York City, where Linda McCartney also received treatment. McCartney
recently helped raise $150,000 at a benefit in New York for the
Garland Appeal, an organization that supports cancer research with
no animal testing. A 360-page ''Beatles Anthology,'' written by
McCartney, George Harrison and Ringo Starr, will be published in
the fall. McCartney was born on June 18, 1942.
</P>
<P>
   Country singer Kathy Mattea, born on June 21, 1959, has chosen
to embrace maturity with her new ''The Innocent Years'' CD (Mercury
Records). Most of the songs on the album are about what's important
as youth fades, although the wry breakup song ''BFD'' is tacked on
at the end to show that she hasn't lost her sense of humor.
Mattea's folk-based country music has proved durable since she made
it big in the late 1980s with ''Eighteen Wheels and a Dozen
Roses.'' ''I'm not 13. I can't be LeAnn Rimes,'' Mattea says. ''My
job is to be me, and do it with as much dignity as I can.''
</P>
<P>
   Celebrity birthdays June 18-24:
</P>
<P>
   June 18: Musician Paul McCartney is 58. Movie critic Roger Ebert
is 58. Actress Isabella Rossellini is 48. Actress Carol Kane is 48.
Singer Alison Moyet is 39. Singer Nathan Morris of Boyz II Men is
29.
</P>
<P>
   June 19: Actress Nancy Marchand (''The Sopranos'') is 72.
Actress Gena Rowlands is 64. Actress Phylicia Rashad (''Cosby'') is
52. Singer Ann Wilson of Heart is 50. Actress Kathleen Turner is
46. Singer Mark DeBarge of DeBarge is 41. Singer-dancer Paula Abdul
is 38.
</P>
<P>
   June 20: Country guitarist Chet Atkins is 76. Actor Martin
Landau is 69. Actress Olympia Dukakis is 69. Actor Danny Aiello is
67. Actor John Mahoney (''Frasier'') is 60. Singer-composer Brian
Wilson of the Beach Boys is 58. Home repair show host Bob Vila is
54. Singer Lionel Richie is 51. Actor John Goodman is 48. Singer
Cyndi Lauper is 47. Actress Nicole Kidman is 33.
</P>
<P>
   June 21: Actress Maureen Stapleton is 75. Singer Ray Davies of
the Kinks is 56. Actress Meredith Baxter (''Family Ties'') is 53.
Actor Michael Gross (''Family Ties'') is 53. Country singer Kathy
Mattea is 41. Actress Juliette Lewis is 27.
</P>
<P>
   June 22: Actor Ralph Waite (''The Waltons'') is 72. Singer-actor
Kris Kristofferson is 64. Actor Michael Lerner is 59. Actress Meryl
Streep is 51. Actress Lindsay Wagner is 51. Actor Graham Greene is
48. Actress Amy Brenneman (''Judging Amy'') is 36. Singer Steven
Page of Barenaked Ladies is 30.
</P>
<P>
   June 23: Country singer June Carter Cash is 71. Actress Frances
McDormand is 43. Musician Steve Shelley of Sonic Youth is 38.
Actress Selma Blair (''Zoe'') is 28. Singer Virgo Williams of
Ghostown DJs is 25.
</P>
<P>
   June 24: Actress Michele Lee is 58. Musician Mick Fleetwood of
Fleetwood Mac is 58. Musician Jeff Beck is 56. Actor Peter Weller
is 53. Musician John Illsley of Dire Straits is 51. Reggae singer
Derrick Simpson of Black Uhuru is 50. Singer Astro of UB40 is 43.
Actress Sherry Stringfield is 33.
</P>
