<HEADLINE> NYC Firefighter in Hot Water  </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
   NEW YORK (AP) -- A New York City firefighter was in hot water
Wednesday for his guest appearance on the saucy HBO program ''Sex
and The City.''
</P>
<P>
   In the June 4 season premiere of the Golden Globe-winning
comedy, Michael Lombardi, 38, played a fireman engaged in a brief
but steamy affair with the character played by Kim Cattrall.
</P>
<P>
   Fire Commissioner Thomas Von Essen said in a statement Wednesday
that he would not comment on the discussions with Lombardi, a
12-year veteran.
</P>
<P>
   ''The department is, however, in the process of reviewing our
outside authorization policy to ensure that firefighters and fire
officers exercise discretion when performing outside employment,''
Von Essen said.
</P>
<P>
   The Uniformed Firefighters Association, which represents
Lombardi, said it would ''vigorously represent'' the actor/fireman
if any disciplinary action were taken by the department.
</P>
<P>
   Lombardi had some notoriety before his appearance on the show.
He appeared in People magazine's 1998 issue on the ''Sexiest Men
Alive'' and in the fire department's 1999 ''Firehouse Hunks''
calendar.
</P>
</TEXT>
