<HEADLINE> Big Movers in the Stock Market  </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
   NEW YORK (AP) -- Stocks that were moving substantially or trading
heavily Wednesday on the New York Stock Exchange and Nasdaq Stock
Market.
</P>
<P>
NYSE
</P>
<P>
Seagram Co. Ltd., up $7.125 at $60.125
</P>
<P>
   The company confirmed it is in talks with French conglomerate
Vivendi SA and its pay-television unit Canal Plus. Published
reports said the discussion involves a possible bid for Seagram
valued at more than $30 billion in stock.
</P>
<P>
Charles Schwab Corp., up $2.875 at $32.875
</P>
<P>
   The brokerage firm said its trading volume, measured in daily
average trades, rose 28 from May 1999 to May 2000. But as a result
of a slump in volume in the broad market, the number of daily
average trades fell 37 percent from April to May.
</P>
<P>
Midas Inc., down $4 at $21
</P>
<P>
   The automotive service chain expects second-quarter earnings to
be below analysts' expectations of 81 cents a share. Midas cited a
delay in the launch of its New Midas program, as well as cool and
rainy weather that hurt retail sales.
</P>
<P>
Wynn's International Inc., up $9.375 at $22.625
Parker Hannifin Corp., down $2.563 at $37.938
</P>
<P>
   Parker Hannifin agreed to buy the heavy-industry
sealing-products company for $23 a share, or about $429.87 million.
Parker Hannifin will also assume $59 million in Wynn's debt.
</P>
<P>
NASDAQ
</P>
<P>
CMGI Inc., up $1.50 at $58.125
</P>
<P>
   Late Tuesday, the company reported a loss of $1.53 a share, less
than the $1.83 loss expected by analysts. Also, CMGI backed fiscal
2001 revenue forecasts of $2 billion to $2.5 billion and said it
had enough cash and securities to cover its operations for 31
months.
</P>
<P>
EBay Inc., down $5.25 at $62.75
</P>
<P>
   Wall Street analysts cut earnings estimates for the second half
of 2000, citing the impact of EBay's planned purchase of Half.com
Inc. for as much as $374 million in stock. Half.com is an online
trading exchange.
</P>
<P>
Visual Networks Inc., down $18.375 at $36.25
</P>
<P>
   Janney Montgomery Scott cut its rating on the stock to
''accumulate'' from ''buy.'' Visual Networks provides network
infrastructure for the Internet.
</P>
<P>
TiVo Inc., up $12.234 at $33.797
</P>
<P>
   TiVo's technology features will be included in AOLTV, America
Online's foray into interactive television. In addition, AOL will
invest up to $200 million in TiVo. The deal will allow TiVo to
accelerate revenue growth as the company makes the TiVo service a
bundled product with AOLTV.
</P>
