<HEADLINE> Series of Quakes Rock So. Calif.  </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
   EL CENTRO, Calif. (AP) -- More than three dozen earthquakes,
including a magnitude-4.3 temblor, rocked southern Imperial County
on Wednesday, but there were no reports of injuries or damage.
</P>
<P>
   The first quake, with a preliminary magnitude of 4.2, hit at
noon about 7 miles northeast of El Centro, said Kate Hutton, a
seismologist at the California Institute of Technology in Pasadena.
</P>
<P>
   Within three hours, it was followed by more than three dozen
aftershocks, including 14 greater than magnitude-3.0.
</P>
<P>
   The region in southeastern California is between the San Andreas
Fault and the Imperial Fault, which was responsible for a
magnitude-6.9 quake in 1940 and a 6.5 quake in 1979.
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
