<HEADLINE> Former Hospital Worker Arrested  </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
   SALISBURY, Md. (AP) -- A former hospital blood worker was
arrested Wednesday and charged with stealing pain medication from
patients' intravenous tubes.
</P>
<P>
   Police said Dawn Wood-Bullard, 36, was caught last month using a
syringe to siphon the drug Demerol from patients' IV tubes.
</P>
<P>
   Wood-Bullard was placed on administrative leave without pay, but
authorities said she returned to the hospital Tuesday night dressed
as a worker and allegedly siphoned morphine from the IV tubing of
two more patients. A worker recognized Wood-Bullard and called
security.
</P>
<P>
   The hospital said no patients were harmed in any of the
incidents.
</P>
<P>
   Wood-Bullard was accused of trespassing, theft, and reckless
endangerment, among other charges. She was held on $45,000 bond at
the Wicomico County Detention Center.
</P>
</TEXT>
