after interviewing both of them, arrested Matt Whiteside on a
domestic violence charge, sheriff's spokesman Ron Reina said.
</P>
<P>
   ''It's been resolved between us. It was resolved the next
morning,'' Whiteside said. ''It's fine. We don't want it to be an
embarrassment for the ballclub. It was unfortunate incident that
happened at the wrong time and the wrong place.''
</P>
