<HEADLINE> Two students hospitalized after being attacked by 25 other teens  </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	   WYCKOFF, N.J. (AP) - A group of about 25 teens severely beat
other two high school students with baseball bats, boards and pipes
outside a home here Tuesday, police said.
</P>
<P>
   Both 17-year-olds who were beaten were hospitalized with one
undergoing a CAT scan to determine if he suffered brain damage,
according to police.
</P>
<P>
   That teen had a damaged eye socket, a possible broken nose, and
cuts that required stitches, police said. The other suffered
bruises and cuts. Both were treated at The Valley Hospital in
Ridgewood and released.
</P>
<P>
   Police said the injured teens are from Ridgefield Park and
Westwood and attend Don Bosco High School in Ramsey.
</P>
<P>
   The attack came after the two took offense at a rumor
circulating about one of the boy's cousins and went to confront a
youth they thought was responsible for spreading at a house on
Demarest Avenue, police said.
</P>
<P>
   When they got there, they were met with the group of 25 teens
who had the weapons, police said.
